tldr: The user wanted to add a database and an admin dashboard to their sleep
  questionnaire application. The project involved updating demographics,
  implementing a Prisma schema for responses, creating API routes for data
  management and CSV export, and building a simple password-protected admin
  dashboard. The authentication system was initially custom but later simplified
  using Next.js middleware.
overview: The user's intent was to enhance their existing sleep questionnaire
  application by adding robust data persistence and an administrative interface.
  The approach involved integrating a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) via Prisma to
  store questionnaire responses, including denormalized demographic data for
  easy retrieval. Key decisions included adopting a simple password-based
  authentication for the admin dashboard and leveraging Next.js middleware for
  efficient route protection. The outcome is a fully functional backend for data
  storage and retrieval, complemented by a basic admin dashboard, ready for
  deployment.
